    "body": "\nCurrently for some code (there's `tests/errors/cpdef_vars.pyx`) the error message looks like\n\n```\nCython/Compiler/Nodes.py\n1560:                    error(self.pos, \"Variables cannot be declared with 'cpdef'. Use 'cdef' instead.\")\n```\n\n\nWe can change it to say `use 'cdef' or 'cdef public' instead.` (because usually `cpdef` means \"make visible to Python\", which `cdef public` does over `cdef`)\n\nShould be just a 1-line change.",
